Papers are drawn as flat sheets that flips on movement, sort of like flying rugs.
I also considered using paper airplanes, but ultimately these flat sheets won out because:
+ The flipping movement adds variety, such that papers move at variable speeds.
+ Flat sheets enable a "cut" animation with scissors, see add_papers.pl.
+ Paper airplanes are hard to identify as paper airplanes from a top down view.
Scissors' blades are constantly opening and closing as it moves. Any resemblance to
Scissorman from the 1996 PlayStation game "Clock Tower" is purely coincidental.
